# Hardware Rules

Initial hardware target: Minew ESL test kit, white-labeled as LotSync. Minew is an adapter implementation—not a business dependency.

## Adapter Boundaries

```
ESLService → RendererAdapter → TransportAdapter → Gateway → ESL
```

Never: `VehicleService → Minew API`

Business logic outputs `LabelPayload` only. Provider-specific rendering and gateway transport stay behind adapters.

## MVP Rendering Path

Phase 1: use Minew local/on-prem renderer if available (`MinewLocalRenderer`).
Phase 2: build `LotSyncRenderer` for vendor independence.
Do not write raw e-paper hex streams for MVP unless no local renderer exists.

## MVP Transport Path

Phase 1: `MinewLocalTransport` over gateway LAN API/HTTP/MQTT.
Minew cloud must not be required for core operation when local APIs are available.

## Dealer-Facing

Dealers buy LotSync hardware kits. Do not surface underlying vendor names in dashboard, mobile app, onboarding, or label templates.

## Future Providers

Minew, Hanshow, SES-imagotag, SoluM—each gets its own renderer and transport adapter. Custom hardware only after demand is proven.
